<div class="col two-sm last" id="ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_PlaceHolderMain_contentColumn2">
<div class="panel">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<h3>Travel information</h3>
    Pilgrim Hospital is located near to the centre of Boston, on one of the main roads out of the town.<br/>It can be accessed by walking away from the main shopping centre along Spilsby Road and Sibsey Road, a walk taking 20 minutes or so.Buses run regularly to Pilgrim Hospital, Boston from Boston town centre and nearby villages.<br/>There is a bus stop handily located on the hospital site for ease of access.<br/>Bus timetables can be obtained from Lincolnshire County Council.


</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="panel">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<h3>Parking</h3>
<p>Patient car parking at Pilgrim Hospital costs £1.70 for 0-1 hours, £4.20 for 1-4 hours and £5 for over 4 hours. A daily charge of £1.90 per day has been implemented for Blue Badge holders. Concessions are available for those receiving some benefits, cancer patients and regular visitors. You can also pay using the good2go app.</p>
